
PWM Resource Dependency Tree

- group
	
	- user
		
		- workload

			[container]

		- volume

			- workload

				[container]

			[physicaldata]

	- workload

		[container]

	- volume

		- workload

			[container]

		[physicaldata]
	
	- storage

		[physicaldata]

		- volume

			- workload

			[physicaldata]

	- node

		- workload

			[container]

		- volume (local)

			- workload

			[physicaldata]

		- cpu

			- workload

		- gpu

			- workload

	- network

		



So, on delete

group.delete() -> [user, storage, node].delete()
user.delete() -> [workload, volume] 
storage.delete() -> [volume].delete()
node.delete() -> [workload, volume, cpu, gpu].delete()

So, on create

workload.create() -> [user, group].verify()
volume.create() -> [storage, user, group].verify()
storage.create() -> [group].verify()
node.create() -> [group].verify()


Cluster actions on delete

workload -> stop
volume -> remove data


On delete

delete -> [drain (aka. stop), _delete]




